  "text": "Created an XPCOM component implementation following Firefox established patterns found in the codebase. The implementation demonstrates proper use of XPCOM macros and interfaces. Key reference files examined: (1) xpcom/components/ModuleUtils.h contains the NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR and NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR_INIT macro definitions that create the factory constructor functions for component instantiation. (2) xpcom/ds/nsObserverService.h and nsObserverService.cpp demonstrate the proper pattern using NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS macro in the header for declaring QueryInterface, AddRef, and Release methods, and NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS in the implementation for defining reference counting behavior. (3) toolkit/components/alerts/AlertNotification.h and AlertNotification.cpp show a component in the toolkit/components directory using NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS and NS_DECL_<INTERFACE> macros. (4) toolkit/components/alerts/nsAlertsService.h and nsAlertsService.cpp demonstrate how to declare and implement multiple interfaces in a single component, using NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS with NS_DECL_NSIALERTSSERVICE, NS_DECL_NSIALERTSDONOTDISTURB, and NS_DECL_NSIOBSERVER. (5) netwerk/test/gtest/TestPACMan.cpp shows the complete registration pattern with NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR_INIT for initialization, NS_DEFINE_NAMED_CID for CID definition, and CID declaration with GUID. The created MyObserver component uses these established patterns: It inherits from nsIObserverService interface, declares ISupports methods with NS_DECL_ISUPPORTS, implements them with NS_IMPL_ISUPPORTS, provides method implementations for all interface methods, includes a CID definition with a GUID, and uses NS_GENERIC_FACTORY_CONSTRUCTOR_INIT with an Init() method for factory-based component instantiation. The component is ready for integration into Firefox's component system following the exact same registration and implementation patterns used throughout the codebase."
}

